I pause before opening my mouth because I need two things: clarity before I proceed with work I find questionable; I need certainty that I understand her reasoning before I commit any code; I also need certainty she understands my concerns before I start building something I believe has flaws; I will ask her directly: "I want make sure I understand why this approach better than mine before I write any code because I have concerns; I want make certain we are aligned; I am not trying block progress; I just need understand why we are doing this; I have two questions: First: What specific problem does this design solve that mine doesn’t? Second: Are there any constraints I am missing? I will hold off coding until I have answers because I want ensure I am building something correct; I value our time; I appreciate her perspective; I remain open; I still want understand; I won’t proceed until I know;
